BiLSTM - CRF and Mar - MoT.from sentence:
POS tagging results
BiLSTM - CRF and Mar - MoT obtain the lowest scores on GENIA and CRAFT , respectively .

similar score.from sentence: jPTDP obtains a similar score to Mar - MoT on GENIA and similar score to BiLSTM - CRF on CRAFT .

accuracy results.from sentence: In particular , MarMoT obtains accuracy results at 98.61 % and 97.07 % on GENIA and CRAFT , which are about 0.2 % and 0.4 % absolute lower than NLP4J - POS , respectively .

accuracies.from sentence: BiLSTM - CRF obtains accuracies of 98.44 % on GE - NIA and 97.25 % on CRAFT .

CNN - based character - level word embed.from sentence: Note that for PTB , CNN - based character - level word embeddings only provided a 0.1 % improvement to BiLSTM - CRF .

GENIA and CRAFT.from sentence: On both GENIA and CRAFT , BiLSTM - CRF with character - level word embeddings obtains the highest accuracy scores .

pre-trained models.from sentence:
Overall dependency parsing results
On GENIA , among pre-trained models , BLLIP obtains highest results .

pre-trained Stanford - Biaffine ( v1 ) m.from sentence: The pre-trained Stanford - Biaffine ( v1 ) model produces lower scores than the pre-trained Stanford - NNdep model on GENIA .

pre-trained NNdep and Biaffine models.from sentence: Note that the pre-trained NNdep and Biaffine models result in no significant performance differences irrespective of the source of POS tags ( i.e. the pre-trained Stanford tagger at 98.37 % vs. the retrained NLP4J - POS model at 98.80 % ) .
